        <p>My name is Ruben Guzman and along with my wife, Patty, we own the new Original Pancake House in Upper Arlington.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row letter-paragraph">
      <div class="col-12">
        <p>And we don’t just work here. Upper Arlington is our home too. We live a few blocks away and our daughter is enrolled at nearby Jones Middle School. Go Golden Bears!</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row letter-paragraph">
      <div class="col-12">
        <p>Our entire family shares an impassioned appreciation of the culinary arts, which is why we fell in love with The Original Pancake House. This is a brand that does things the right way – choice ingredients, handcrafted recipes and hospitable service. No detail seems too small.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row letter-paragraph">
      <div class="col-12">
        <p>However, it’s one thing to love a restaurant, but it’s entirely different to open your own. Which is why you need a great partner, and I have one in my wife. This became possible because of her.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row letter-paragraph">
      <div class="col-12">
        <p>While we were living in the Republic of Panama, Patty noticed a great void of quality and unique breakfast options and suggested we do something about it.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row letter-paragraph">
      <div class="col-12">
        <p>Having spent nearly 20 years as a franchisee for the Dublin, OH based Wendy’s, I was familiar with the restaurant industry and decided to contact Jon Liss, a decision marker for the OPH brand at that time to discuss our options.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row letter-paragraph">
      <div class="col-12">
        <p>Over time, we developed a great personal friendship with Jon and we knew that we wanted to be a part of the OPH family. We entertained the idea of bringing the OPH franchise to Panama, but decided to take a chance and return to the United States to begin this new venture in central Ohio.</p>
